Yeah I think this goes into the category of:<p><pre><code>  Patient: &quot;Doctor, when I bend my arm backward, it hurts!&quot;

  Doctor: &quot;Stop doing that.&quot;
</code></pre>
Doesn&#x27;t mean that using your arm is a bad idea.

Nice and clean solution. I usually write the version string of a program with a git pre-commit hook.<p>Like this:<p><pre><code>    HASH=&quot;$(git rev-parse --short HEAD)&quot;
    sed &#x27;s/Version = .*/Version = &quot;&#x27;&quot;$HASH&quot;&#x27;+&quot;/&#x27; -i version.go
    git add version.go</code></pre>
